## Discussion Summary

**1. Team Agreement**  
The team agreed on a fixed weekly meeting time of Monday 7:00 PM AEST to accommodate different time zones. Carlos will send a calendar invite to all members. Communication between meetings will be via a shared Microsoft Teams channel created by Carlos.

**2. Project Brief Review**  
The team reviewed the MediCare Plus Clinic case study together. Key observations noted:  
- The clinic operates a hybrid environment across two physical sites and Microsoft Azure  
- Several critical misconfigurations have already been identified in the case study (permissive NSG rules, missing MFA, public Blob Storage)  
- The project must align with Australian healthcare privacy legislation including the Privacy Act 1988 and the My Health Records Act 2012  
- A regulatory audit is approaching, which sets the urgency context for all deliverables  

**3. Roles and Artefact Ownership**  
Team confirmed the following ownership, consistent with the Project Proposal:  
- Carlos Gomez: Project Leader, Security Posture Report, Remediation & Recommendations Report  
- Abdullah Naeem: Stakeholder Interview Plan & Summary, Risk Assessment Table, Risk Assessment Report  
- Kishan Patel: Cloud Security Architecture Review, System Architecture Diagram, Security Policies Pack  

**4. GitHub Repository**  
Carlos created the group repository at github.com/naeemabdulla/MediCare-Plus-Clinic-Network-Security-Assessment during the meeting. Commit conventions were agreed:  
- Format: [initials] type: short description  
- Types: add | update | fix | review | draft  
- All members to commit at least once per week  
- README to be maintained by Carlos and updated at each milestone  

**5. Folder Structure**  
